How does oncolytic virus therapy work?

Oncolytic virus therapy works by using genetically modified viruses to selectively infect and destroy cancer cells.

Are oncolytic virus therapies safe?

While promising, safety concerns regarding genetically modified viruses remain a challenge and require further research.

What types of cancer can be treated with oncolytic virus therapies?

Oncolytic viruses are being tested in various cancers including melanoma, glioma, and other solid tumors.

